The results in the new datasets are summarized by the nearest numerical distance from a zip-code 
boundary to a park boundary in meters as ‘nearest_distance_m’. The visual results are a dynamic 
map that provides the zip-code and the numerical value for the nearest distance to a park 
boundary and the name of that park with the use of the hover tool. The visual results on 
the map is a choropleth map ranging from dark green as lower values and light green for the
higher values for distance to nearest park. More visual results would be the scale bar along 
the right hand side with values in meters to help navigate the user for the values being 
displayed on the map. The analysis of the visualizations show a concentration of zip-codes 
in the North Las Vegas region that has higher distances to the nearest park suggesting those
zip-codes would benefit from some green space and park attention from policy makers.
